    "created_at": "2012-11-12T17:47:32Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-11-12T17:47:32Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "People messing around with easy_install and pip is not going to get us to 'wide adoption' - there are far too many problems there, and it's beyond our scope to fix them. There are better installation methods we recommend, including: \n- Python distros like Anaconda & EPD Free, which include everything you need to run the notebook.\n- Serious package managers like apt which can reliably install all the dependencies.\n- Using the notebook on a server where it's already set up - [NotebookCloud](https://notebookcloud.appspot.com/login) is a prototype of this approach, and there will be better offerings as development continues.\n"
  },
