    "updated_at": "2012-11-12T17:53:16Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I can buy the \"we should go full-force with distro package managers\" argument, but then this needs to be the recommended installation method rather than easy_install.\n\nFor what it's worth, running `pip install ipython[zmq,qtconsole,notebook,test]` on my OSX was all I had to do to get it working. I suspect the same thing would be true on my Linux box. That's pretty swell and it would be a shame to bury this fact with more complicated instructions.\n"
